        <p class="body-p">In 2009, the records of the 1969 Delta State sit-in, "one of Delta State's most important insight into commemoration: its ability to heal," conducted by asking students questions about their families and connecting them to storytellers directly affects how the stories come to be presented in each exhibit. Who were the storytellers, and what did it take for them to share their stories?</p>
